Subject: [PATCH 5/5] feat: multi-node deployment: nginx LB, scalable web
 replicas, single indexer worker

Fase 4 of the plain-text manager plan:
- docker-compose.multinode.yml: nginx entrypoint, N stateless web
  replicas (read-only index mount, worker_mode), one indexer worker,
  Redis (AOF) for jobs + shared L2 cache, PostgreSQL
- deploy/nginx.conf resolves the app service per-request through
  Docker's DNS so round-robin follows --scale without reloads
- Makefile targets docker-up-multinode (REPLICAS=n) / docker-down-multinode
- docs/SCALING.md: the three supported topologies, RAM budget per
  profile, single-writer rule, and the (idioma, tema) partitioning plan
  for >50M chunks

